These shortcuts live in muscle memory after a week. Print this page if you need to.

## Core Controls

| Shortcut | Action |
|----------|--------|
| `Esc` | Stop generation mid-response |
| `Esc` + `Esc` | Open [rewind menu](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/interactive-mode) to restore previous states |
| `Ctrl+C` | Cancel current input |
| `Ctrl+D` | Exit session |
| `?` | Show all shortcuts for your environment |

Double-tap `Esc` on an empty prompt to rewind the conversation. Note: this resets messages only. File changes stay on disk. Pair with git or ask Claude to undo explicitly.

## Screen & History

| Shortcut | Action |
|----------|--------|
| `Ctrl+L` | Clear terminal screen (conversation persists) |
| `Ctrl+R` | Reverse search through prompt history |
| `Up/Down` | Navigate previous inputs |
| `Ctrl+O` | [Toggle verbose output](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/interactive-mode) (shows tool usage details) |
| `Ctrl+G` | Open prompt in your system's text editor |

`Ctrl+O` is gold for debugging. When Claude goes quiet mid-task, toggle verbose to see what it's actually doing.

## Mode & Model Switching

| Shortcut | Action |
|----------|--------|
| `Shift+Tab` | Cycle: Normal -> Auto-Accept -> Plan Mode |
| `Alt+M` | Same as Shift+Tab (alternative binding) |
| `Option+P` (Mac) / `Alt+P` | Switch model while typing |
| `Tab` | Toggle extended thinking (may require `/config` on some versions) |

When you're mid-prompt and realize this needs Opus 4.5 instead of Sonnet 4.5, hit `Option+P` to switch without retyping.

## Input Methods

### Images

`Ctrl+V` pastes images from clipboard. On Mac, this is `Ctrl+V`, not `Cmd+V`. On Windows, use `Alt+V`. Linux support varies by terminal.

### Multiline Input

| Method | How |
|--------|-----|
| Universal | `\` then `Enter` |
| macOS | `Option+Enter` |
| After setup | `Shift+Enter` (run `/terminal-setup` first) |
| Control sequence | `Ctrl+J` (line feed) |

The `/terminal-setup` command configures Shift+Enter for [iTerm2, VS Code, Kitty, Alacritty, Zed, and Warp](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/interactive-mode). Other terminals need manual configuration.

## Quick Prefixes

| Prefix | Action |
|--------|--------|
| `/` | Slash command (built-in or custom) |
| `#` | Add instruction directly to CLAUDE.md |
| `!` | Execute bash command without Claude interpreting it |
| `@` | File path autocomplete |

The `!` prefix runs commands raw. `! npm test` adds the command and output to context without Claude trying to "help."

## Background Execution

| Shortcut | Action |
|----------|--------|
| `Ctrl+B` | Push running bash command to background |
| `/bashes` | List and manage background tasks |

Tmux users: press `Ctrl+B` twice since tmux intercepts the first one.

Background commands are assigned IDs like `bash_1`, `bash_2`. Claude can keep working while your dev server runs.

